This paper deals with the problem of minimum-weight triangulation, which is a well-studied problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses linear programming formulations and approximation algorithms, which are common topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.OC (Optimization and Control). The paper also mentions the integrality gap, which is a concept in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Finally, the paper discusses heuristics and exact algorithms, which are relevant to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
